    "Her travelogues published during this period discussed art at length.": [],
    "Her husband now established in Canadian politics, she made a brief trip to North America for appearances, and returned to Europe with an understanding to live independently of him with a small yearly stipend.": [],
    "In 1840, Jameson wrote an introduction to the English translation of <em>Peter Paul Rubens</em> by <a href=\"/waageng\">Gustav Friedrich Waagen</a>.": [],
    "In it she argued for the broader, German interpretation of images over the rather pedestrian view most British art critics took.": [
        [
