    "She was clearly familiar with the writing (and bibliography) of <a href=\"/rumohrk\">Karl Friedrich von Rumohr</a>.": [],
    "Her iconography was in part the inspiration for <a href=\"/kaftalg\">George Kaftal</a> and his work on Italian saints.": [],
    "Though her writing reputation today as an art historian rests today upon her <em>Sacred and Legendary Art</em> volumes, Jameson's championing of the \"primitive\" schools of art, i.e., the late-medieval and early Renaissance art, is her greatest contribution to the history of art history.": []
